content: This app is designed to be run locally to develop a local software project. It will be hosted on GitHub. How should people run it? You clone the repository, then what?

So they should npm run dev? That makes more sense than npm run build and npm run start?

Just to be clear, the ballistic app is used to develop a different software project. It won't be used to develop itself.
See the initial_welcome_message quick start guide for information on how to use the app. Update readme accordingly.
What's the MIT license? Does that make the most sense?
